@page "/documentation/introduction/gettingstarted"

<div class="container mx-auto p-6 font-mono">
    <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Getting Started with AiDesigner</h2>
        
        <!-- Introduction Section -->
        <div class="mb-4 dark:!bg-gray-700 bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Introduction</h3>
            <p>AiDesigner is a visual programming tool that allows users to design, create, and manage AI-based projects through a block-based interface.</p>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Setting Up AiDesigner -->
        <div class="mb-4 dark:!bg-gray-700 bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Setting Up AiDesigner</h3>
            <p>Follow the steps below to set up AiDesigner:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-4 ml-6 mb-2">
                <li>Just create an account in the top right corner.</li>
                <li>Go to the library page.</li>
                <li>Then create a new projects.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Creating a New Project -->
        <div class="mb-4 dark:!bg-gray-700 bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Creating a New Project</h3>
            <p>From the main dashboard, you can start a new project:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-4 ml-6 mb-2">
                <li>Click on 'Add Program' to create a new project.</li>
                <li>Name your project and provide an optional description.</li>
                <li>Start adding blocks from the library to design your AI flow.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Using the Marketplace -->
        <div class="mb-4 dark:!bg-gray-700 bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Using the Marketplace</h3>
            <p>The Marketplace is a hub where users can discover, purchase, or share AI blocks and programs designed by the community.</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-4 ml-6 mb-2">
                <li>Browse through a wide variety of AI blocks and programs available for use.</li>
                <li>Filter and search based on your specific needs.</li>
                <li>Download the blocks you need for your project.</li>
                <li>Share your own custom-designed blocks.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Using the Vault -->
        <div class="mb-4 dark:!bg-gray-700 bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Using the Vault</h3>
            <p>The Vault is a repository of blocks or programs sourced from the marketplace. These are always in a deployed state, allowing users to instantly integrate and use them via an API endpoint.</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-4 ml-6 mb-2">
                <li>Access pre-configured blocks and programs directly from the marketplace.</li>
                <li>Easily integrate custom blocks into your projects for streamlined construction and development.</li>
                <li>No need for additional deployment; simply integrate into your project and call the API.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Custom Blocks -->
        <div class="mb-4 dark:!bg-gray-700 bg-gray-100 p-4 rounded">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Creating Custom Blocks</h3>
            <p>If the built-in blocks don't meet your needs, create your own:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-4 ml-6 mb-2">
                <li>Click on 'Add Custom Block' to start designing your own block.</li>
                <li>Define the inputs, outputs, and functionality as needed.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
